description:
&lt;p&gt;Therapy Services have an exciting opportunity for a band 8a Therapy Service Lead to join our team.&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will support the Directorate by providing therapy leadership to in-patient Physiotherapy and Occupational Therapy Services, covering Spinal Injuries, Neuro Rehab and Stroke, Inpatient wards, Specialist Outpatient Services and Palliative Care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are entering an exciting phase in the development of therapy services and we are looking for an individual with drive and excellent change management skills to join our team to assist in delivering our exciting vision for the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsible to the Assistant Director -Therapies, the In-patient Therapy Lead will draw from a broad range of experience as a senior therapist to provide expert therapy leadership within the directorate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must have the character, skills and ability to inspire and develop those around them to meet their potential, a proven track record of operationally managing therapy services, whilst ensuring the delivery of a high quality service which is clinically safe and delivers the best experience to patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must be registered with HCPC, have senior therapy experience in a hospital setting; display exceptional written and verbal communication skills and be highly motivated to deliver on key strategic outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details please contact Deirdre Linnane, Assistant Director-Therapies on 01924 541475 or via email Deirdre.linnane@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
